---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="6-Letter Words with X — Top Scoring Scrabble Words (2026)" description="Complete guide to 6-letter X words for Scrabble. SUFFIX (19pts), SPHINX (18pts), VORTEX (16pts), BOXING (16pts) and 40+ more ranked by score." keywords="6 letter words with x, scrabble x words, six letter x words, suffix scrabble, high scoring x words, x words scrabble list">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"6-Letter Words with X — Top Scoring Scrabble Words","description":"Complete guide to 6-letter X words for Scrabble. SUFFIX (19pts), SPHINX (18pts), VORTEX (16pts), and 40+ more ranked by score tier.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/6-letter-words-with-x"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the highest-scoring 6-letter X word in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SUFFIX scores 19 points, making it the highest-scoring common 6-letter X word. It benefits from both the X(8) and double-F tiles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How should you place X for maximum points in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Place X on a Double or Triple Letter Score whenever possible. X is worth 8 points, so a DLS makes it 16 and a TLS makes it 24. Combine with word multipliers for massive scores."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the best 6-letter X words without rare tiles?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"TAXING (14pts), BOXING (16pts), EXOTIC (15pts), and VORTEX (16pts) all use common tiles alongside X, making them realistic plays with typical racks."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">6-Letter Words with X — Complete Scrabble Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The X tile is worth 8 points — making it the third-highest value tile in Scrabble after Q and Z. Six-letter X words combine that power with enough length to reach premium squares. Here's your complete scoring guide.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SUFFIX top score</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">40+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6-letter X words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">X tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">38</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SUFFIX on DWS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tier 1: 16+ Points</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The highest-scoring 6-letter X words combine X with other premium-value consonants. SUFFIX leads with its double-F bonus stacking.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SUFFIX — 19 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">S(1) + U(1) + F(4) + F(4) + I(1) + X(8). Double-F stacks beautifully.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SPHINX — 18 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">S(1) + P(3) + H(4) + I(1) + N(1) + X(8). Mythical creature, real points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">VORTEX — 16 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V(4) + O(1) + R(1) + T(1) + E(1) + X(8). Strong mid-game play.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">BOXING — 16 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B(3) + O(1) + X(8) + I(1) + N(1) + G(2). Common word, solid score.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tier 2: 14–15 Points</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">These words use everyday tiles alongside X. They're easier to form with a standard rack and still deliver strong point totals.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">EXOTIC — 15 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Strikingly unusual. E(1) + X(8) + O(1) + T(1) + I(1) + C(3).</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">TAXING — 14 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Physically demanding. T(1) + A(1) + X(8) + I(1) + N(1) + G(2).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More 6-Letter X Words</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Beyond the top scorers, these words fill out your X-word vocabulary for different board situations:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXCITE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXPAND</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXPORT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EXTERN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OXYGEN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">17pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TUXEDO</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Board Placement Strategy</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">X at 8 points benefits enormously from letter multipliers. A single DLS turns X into 16 points of contribution — more than most entire words.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> X on a DLS = 16 points from one tile. On TLS = 24 points. Always scout the board for letter multipliers before placing X.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> SUFFIX on a DWS = 38 points. Position the word so X or the double-F lands on a letter multiplier for maximum stacking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> Unlike Z, X appears in many common English words. You rarely need to force an obscure play — BOXING, TAXING, and EXOTIC are all everyday vocabulary.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">X is more versatile than Z or Q because it appears in <span class="text-white font-medium">common words like BOXING, TAXING, and EXOTIC</span>. You rarely get stuck with X — there's almost always a solid 6-letter play available.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/4-letter-words-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">4-Letter Words with X</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
